The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 August is 2,835 (328.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 August, there were 19 new confirmed cases (2.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 August, there were 18 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 6% (1 extra case).
